    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>195</citedRange> (photo)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>102400</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, pp. <citedRange>197-198</citedRange> (discovery) and p. <citedRange>204</citedRange> (date of base)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>210</citedRange></bibl> (provenance);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.24</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64227"><name nymRef="#Θεύχρηστος">Θεύχρηστος</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62858"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀνάψυξις">Ἀναψύξιος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Theukhrestos fils d'Anapsyxis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Theuchrestos son of Anapsyxis.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Theuchrestos figlio di Anapsyxis.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This inscription was published by Pugliese Carratelli from a photograph only.</p>
                <p>Beschi, who observed the stone for his catalogue of funerary bases, would place it about the middle of III BC. 
                    However, the lettering seems somewhat older.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
